OL,4,CWilliam Orr: The blind postman who
OL,5,Cdelivered a first-class service
OL,6, In the 1920s, postman William Orr
OL,7, walked for miles every day along rural
OL,8, roads to deliver mail, despite the fact
OL,9, that he was registered as blind.
OL,11,FHe was employed as a postal worker at
OL,12,FBalnamore Mill in County Antrim.
OL,14,FDespite his visual impairment, he
OL,15,Fregularly carried mail between the mill
OL,16,Fand the nearest town, Ballymoney, a
OL,17,Fjourney of about two-and-a-half miles.
